text:
West 238th Street (running from lower right hand corner to center background), east from Spuyten Duyvil Road to Broadway, showing, on the latter, the elevated structure of the I.R.T. Van Cortlandt Park subway line. Also shown is a general view eastward, and land being filled for extensive real estate development. The thoroughfares crossing West 238th Street are: Tibbett Ave; Corlear Ave. and Kingsbridge Ave. The vantage point is the N.E. corner of Waldo Ave. and West 238th Street.

May 1926.

Brown Brothers.

A panoramic view northeastward across the car yards of the Interborough Rapid Transit Co.; the elevated structure of the I.R.T. Van Cortlandt Park subway and its 242nd Street station, on Broadway; and Van Cortlandt Park, as seen from the N.E. corner of Waldo Ave. and West 238th Street.

May 1926.

Brown Brothers.
